==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nifty
<hw>nifty</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Very good; excellent; --
an informal term meaning about the same as <er>groovy</er>, sense
1.</def> <mark>[informal, 1960's]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bang-up, bully, cool, corking, cracking, dandy,
great, groovy, keen, neat, not bad(predicate), peachy, slap-up, swell,
smashing.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Stylish; attractive; -- of clothing; <as>as, a
<ex>nifty</ex> outfit</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nifle</ent>⟦br⟧
